    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process that produces a direct positive image on a silver-coated copper plate, invented by Louis-Jacques-Mandé Daguerre of France and Joseph-Nicéphore Niepce in the 1830s. In the process, a copper plate is coated with silver iodide and exposed to light in a camera, then fumed with mercury vapour and fixed with common salt in solution.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso que produce una imagen positiva directa sobre una placa de cobre recubierta de plata, inventado por Louis-Jacques-Mandé Daguerre, de Francia, y Joseph-Nicéphore Niepce en la década de 1830.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eenmalig procédé waarbij een direct positief wordt verkregen op een gepolijste verzilverde, aanvankelijk door jodiumdampen en later in combinatie met broomdampen lichtgevoelig gemaakte koperplaat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052562/Dijk en Zoete, Fotografische Termen en Technieken (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在塗銀的銅版上製作出直接正像的印相法，為法國的路易斯賈克斯曼迪˙達吉瑞（Louis-Jacques-Mandé Daguerre）和約瑟夫尼賽福爾˙尼耶皮斯（Joseph-Nicéphore Niepce）於1830年代所發明。在過程中，塗有碘化銀的銅版在相機中進行曝光，然後以水銀蒸汽燻過，再於食鹽溶劑來固定影像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Processo que produz uma imagem positiva direta em uma placa de cobre revestida de prata, inventado por Louis-Jacques-Mandé Daguerre da França e Joseph-Nicéphore Niepce na década de 1830. No processo, uma placa de cobre é revestida com iodeto de prata e exposta à luz em uma câmera, então vaporizada com vapor de mercúrio e fixada com sal comum em solução. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
